5|$|Sarah Margaret Fuller Ossoli (May 23, 1810 – July 19, 1850), {{commonly}} known as Margaret Fuller, was an <b>American</b> <b>journalist,</b> critic, and women's rights advocate associated with the American transcendentalism movement. She was the first full-time American female book reviewer in journalism. Her book Woman in the Nineteenth Century is considered the first major feminist work in the United States.|$|E
